title: 4 trampled to death in Assam by wild jumbos
description: Four villagers, including two minor boys, were trampled to death by wild elephants in Karbi Anglong in Assam on Thursday, reports Kangkan Kalita. The deceased have been identified as Kania Toria (55), Ribika Kerketta (28), Geseya Kerketta (3) and one-and-a-half year-old Augustin Karmakar. All of them were from Bormanthi village. Forest department officials said the incident took place around noon when Kania and Ribika were cutting grass at an isolated location in Lalubasti area near Bokajan town.

title: Balloons, bands and Santa: Macy's Thanksgiving Parade ushers in NY
description: Beloved characters like Snoopy and SpongeBob SquarePants soared through the skies above New York City on Thursday and bands marched along the streets below as the annual Macy's Thanksgiving Day Parade ushered in the holiday season. The parade started on Manhattan's Upper West Side making its way alongside Central Park in front of big crowds and a national television audience before ending in front of Macy's flagship store on 34th Street. Among the big names performing is Cher, who just released her first Christmas album.

title: PM Modi spots 95-year-old BJP man, draws cheers
description: PM Narendra Modi on Thursday drew cheers from the audience at his poll rally in Deogarh in Rajasthan when he recognised a nonagenarian BJP member, Dharam Chand Derasariya, sitting in the crowd and lauded his contribution to the party. "Derasariya ji has probably given his six decades of his life to propagate this (BJP's) ideology. Today, he is sitting there as a party worker and giving blessings," Modi said. ​​He said it was his last public meeting in the state ahead of the November 25 assembly polls.

title: Voters will make magician Gehlot vanish on December 3: Amit Shah
description: On Friday, the last day of campaigning for the Rajasthan elections, Congress’s Sachin Pilot rebutted PM Modi’s remarks about his late father. “I heard the PM’s statement (about Rajesh Pilot being briefly sidelined by Congress for standing up to the Gandhi family). What he said is far from the truth... Also, no one should be worried about my present or my future. I am confident that my party and the people will take good care of me,” Sachin Pilot said.

title: Mettle vs Metal: Rescuers put lives on the line in dramatic tunnel op
description: Someone in the crowd, waiting like the others around him for the 41 men trapped in the Silkyara tunnel to come out, said, “Bas, ho gaya. Ab bahar niklenge humare log .” A second person chimed in and said, “Very good, very good.” Soon, there was a wave of celebrations. Wednesday: 6 pm. The joy turned out to be premature. The men were still stuck inside. An hour later, at about 7 pm, personnel from the (NDRF) were told the drilling machine had hit metal. It couldn’t plough through it to reach the workers stranded barely meters away.

title: India set to kick off 3 mega defence projects worth Rs 1.4L cr
description: India is now set to give preliminary approval to three mega indigenous projects to manufacture another aircraft carrier, 97 more Tejas fighters and 156 Prachand light combat helicopters, which together will be worth around Rs 1.4 lakh crore. The Rajnath Singh-led defence acquisitions council is likely to take up the ‘acceptance of necessity’ (AoN) — the first step in the procurement process — for the three crucial projects at a meeting slated on November 30, sources told TOI on Thursday.

title: 2 yrs on, govt names SC collegium pick as Bom HC addl judge
description: The law ministry on Thursday notified appointment of advocate Somasekhar Sundaresan as additional judge of the Bombay HC, almost two years after his name was cleared by the Supreme Court collegium. Sundaresan was among five other advocates whose names were reiterated by the apex court collegium this year, brushing aside requests from the Centre for reconsideration of their appointment as judges of different high courts.

title: On last day of campaigning, Gehlot & Pilot rebut PM's claim in one voice
description: Battleground Rajasthan resonated with poll pyrotechnics one last time on Thursday as electioneering closed in a blaze of allegations and counters, including a rare instance of CM Ashok Gehlot and his estranged deputy Sachin Pilot rebutting in one voice PM Narendra Modi's allegation about the latter being “punished” by Congress just like his late father was.  “I heard the PM's statement (about Rajesh Pilot being briefly sidelined by Congress for standing up to the Gandhi family).

title: Dublin: Protesters throng street after knife attack injured 3 children
description: Protests erupted in central Dublin after a knife attack on a 5-year-old girl, a woman, and two other children. The Irish police, not treating the case as terror-related, have identified a man in his 50s as a person of interest. They have a definite line of inquiry and don't seek anyone else. Violent demonstrators attacked the police cordon, causing damage to vehicles and setting a bus and car on fire. Witnesses intervened early on to disarm the attacker. The injured include a woman in her 30s and two children aged 5 and 6.

title: For 1st time since Mahua row, Mamata backs MP
description: Bengal CM Mamata Banerjee broke her silence on the cash-for-query controversy involving Trinamool Congress MP Mahua Moitra on Thursday, rallying behind her and declaring BJP's alleged attempt to oust her from Parliament "a foolish thing to do". "This way, they will end up making her more popular," Mamata said at a party convention in Kolkata, echoing Moitra's claim that the parliamentary ethics committee's report recommending her expulsion had turned her into "Jhansi ki Rani". TMC reinstated Moitra as the party's Krishnanagar district president recently, with Mamata endorsing the appointment.

title: DGCA to make flying passenger-friendly
description: The government plans to review existing DGCA rules to make them more passenger-friendly and ensure airlines provide assistance to passengers affected by delays, cancellations, or denied boarding. IndiGo passengers recently faced issues when they were not flown to their destination as per their original booking, raising questions about consumer rights. The government aims to simplify the rules and display them at airports to inform passengers of their rights and duties. This change is prompted by the resurgence of consumer interest as domestic air traffic surpasses pre-pandemic levels.

title: Decide on setting up panel for delimitation urgently: Supreme Court
description: The Supreme Court on Thursday directed the Union government to decide “with reasonable dispatch” setting up a Delimitation Commission to examine the need to increase seats reserved for Scheduled Castes and Scheduled Tribes in Lok Sabha and state assemblies in view of the addition of scores of communities to the list of SCs and STs after 2001 when the last delimitation exercise was carried out. When additional solicitor general K M Natraj informed the court that nearly 51 communities were added after 2001 to the list of STs till the last census took place in 2011.

title: ‘Flying school tampered with 2 accident-hit planes’ data cards’
description: Red Bird Flight Training illegally removed the Secure Digital (SD) data card from the crashed aircraft at Baramati airport. The card records flight data and engine performance parameters. Red Bird tampered with the SD card and handed it over to the Aircraft Accident Investigation Bureau (AAIB). They repeated this offense when a second aircraft crashed, causing the loss of crucial data. The AAIB preliminary reports revealed these details and also mentioned that Red Bird had multiple accidents in the past months.

title: With ‘heavy heart’, SC agrees to govt plea to defer PMLA hearing
description: After almost two days of hearing on a batch of petitions challenging the validity of some provisions of the Prevention of Money Laundering Act and for review of a 2022 verdict which upheld the law, the Supreme Court on Thursday ordered that the case would have to be heard afresh by a new bench as the Centre pressed for adjournment and the presiding judge is retiring next month. Solicitor general Tushar Mehta said he was “handicapped” and needed some time to respond to the pleas of the petitioners who have expanded their challenge to the 2022 verdict beyond the issues they had initially raised.

title: SC: Governments can’t sit on bills and veto legislative action
description: The Supreme Court has sought to clearly delineate the boundary of action by governors when a bill passed by a state assembly is sent for their assent by ruling that, being titular heads of states, they don’t have the power to veto legislative actions of elected governments or sit indefinitely on bills duly passed by the legislature. The November 10 judgment, passed on a plea by the Mann government in Punjab against governor Banwarilal Purohit, was uploaded on Thursday on the SC website.

title: Pannun: Will let US government speak on 'murder attempt'
description: US-based wanted terrorist Gurpatwant Singh Pannun, an unabashed supporter of Khalistani terrorists, responded to claims of an assassination attempt on him by mercenaries allegedly with an Indian connection. Pannun expressed confidence in the US government's protection and stated that he would let them respond to the threat. He also announced plans to kick off the 'American phase' of the Khalistan Referendum and called for protests at Toronto and Vancouver airports. Pannun admitted to being behind pro-Khalistan graffiti incidents in India and vowed to campaign for the liberation of Punjab from Indian occupation.

title: Hear review plea on gay marriage in open court, petitioners to SC
description: LGBTQIA+ community members on Thursday requested an open court hearing on their petitions seeking review of the Supreme Court’s October 17 judgment rejecting marriage rights for same-sex couples, and tactically based their demand on CJI D Y Chandrachud’s minority opinion – “when there is discrimination, it must be remedied by the courts”. Senior advocate Mukul Rohatgi told a bench led by the CJI that the review petitions, listed for consideration in chambers before a five-judge bench on November 28, must be heard in the open court.

title: Home Guard jawan killed, 5 cops injured in gurdwara clash
Trapped workers just 10-13m away, but snag halts drilling
description: Rescue operation in the Silkyara tunnel to evacuate workers was halted temporarily due to a snag with the auger drilling machine.​ Sources told TOI that the platform on which the auger machine has been mounted, got destabilised after developing some cracks. “Technical teams have been working non-stop to stabilise the 25-tonne platform on which the machine is mounted,” the sources said, adding that drilling is likely to start only after the platform is completely stabilised.

title: Spl Forces soldier wounded in Rajouri op dies; LeT man shot
description: In the ongoing anti-terrorism operation in J&K’s Rajouri district, a Lance Naik from 9 Para (Special Forces) died, bringing the total security casualties to five. The operation led to the killing of two terrorists, including a high-ranking Pakistani commander of Lashkar-e-Taiba (LeT). The fallen soldiers are Captain MV Pranjal, Captain Shubham Gupta, Havildar Abdul Majid, Lance Naik Sanjay Bisht, and paratrooper Sachin Laur. The two frontier districts of Rajouri and Poonch in the Jammu region were declared terrorism-free more than a decade ago, but have recorded 35 fatalities since October 2021.

title: 1st T20I: '3 wickets and an unaccounted six' in thrilling last-over
description: Young left-handed batter Rinku Singh held his nerves despite losing three wickets in three balls, guiding India to a thrilling last-ball two-wicket win over Australia in the first T20I of the five-match series in Visakhapatnam on Thursday. Needing 7 runs off 6 balls, Rinku started off with a four off the first ball followed with a single bringing the equation down to 2 off 4 balls. But fate had different plans as India lost three wickets in the form of Axar Patel, Ravi Bishnoi and Arshdeep Singh in the next three successive deliveries.

title: 1st T20I: Surya, Rinku seal India's highest successful chase
description: Skipper Suryakumar Yadav shrugged off the disappointment of a World Cup final defeat with a captain's knock but it was Rinku Singh's composure that took a young Indian team to a thrilling two-wicket victory in the opening T20I in Visakhapatnam. This was India's highest successful chase in T20 Internationals. The skipper was in belligerent mood making a mockery of a 209-run chase with 42-ball 80 but Rinku's 22 not out off 14 balls saved India from the blushes.

title: Threat to blow up Mumbai T2 Airport in 48 hrs
description: The sender of the mail has placed a demand to pay one million dollars in Bitcoin within 48 hours to avert the blast.

title: Tunnel collapse: Frequent obstacles delay rescue operation
description: Rescue operation in the collapsed portion of Sikyara tunnel was delayed due to frequent obstacles of iron girders. The option of clearing the remaining stretch by experienced manual cutters is under consideration. Auger machine had to be stopped thrice during horizontal drilling. Steel lattice girders have been cut twice using gas cutters. Around 45-47 meters have been covered, with around 17-20 meters remaining.

title: Mystery pneumonia cases: WHO urges China to mask up again
Will Rahul's 'panauti', 'pickpocket' jibes land him in trouble?
Karnataka cabinet nods to withdraw CBI case against DK Shivakumar
description: "Previous BJP govt decision to hand over assets case against D K Shivakumar to CBI is not in accordance with law," PTI quoted the state cabinet as saying.

title: Karnataka told to release 3216 cusecs water to TN for 38 days
description: The Cauvery Water Regulation Committee (CWRC) recommended the Karnataka government to release 3216 cusecs of water every day to Tamil Nadu for 38 days starting November 24, 2023. The committee also stated that Karnataka needs to ensure stipulated quantities of flow as per the Cauvery Water Disputes Tribunal (CWDT) award. In response, Tamil Nadu demanded that Karnataka release 5000 cusecs of water for the next 30 days. The governments of Karnataka and Tamil Nadu have been locked in a protracted tussle over the sharing of Cauvery waters.

title: Watch: Stoinis bursts into laughter after Gaikwad's run out
description: Indian opener Ruturaj Gaikwad suffered an unfortunate run out without facing a ball during the first T20I of the five-match series against Australia in Visakhapatnam on Thursday.

title: Teen stabbing: 'Rarest of rare' case, say police
description: PTI quoted deputy Commissioner of police (Northeast) Joy Tirkey as saying that the apprehended accused, identified as a juvenile, has been captured on CCTV committing the crime.

title: 'Any selector will be tempted…': Nehra on Rohit, Kohli's T20I future
description: The speculation surrounding the future of Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli in T20Is has been the talk of the town, specially within the cricket fraternity, following India's defeat in the World Cup final against Australia. Skipper Rohit and Kohli have been away from the shortest format since India's T20 World Cup semi-final exit in November 2022. Hardik Pandya has mostly led the Indian team in T20Is since then.

title: Watch: Bishnoi knocks over Short with a wrong 'un
description: To watch a wrong 'un delivery is a viewer's delight but to face it is certainly a nightmare for any batter across the globe. Australian opener Matthew Short was one such batter who was at the receiving end when he was beaten all ends up with a gem of a googly delivered by young Indian leg-spinner Ravi Bishnoi during the first T20I of the five-match series. The incident happened in the fifth over of the innings when Bishnoi bowled a nicely tossed up googly, and Short tried to go over the mid-wicket but missed it completely.

title: UP: YouTuber found dead, father alleges murder
description: Malti Devi operated a YouTube channel named 'Malti Chauhan Fun,' boasting an impressive subscriber base of over 6.5 lakh individuals.

title: Ramayan fame Dipika Chikhlia anniversary pics amuse netizens
description: Dipika Chikhlia Topiwala recently posted a cute video with her husband, Hemant Topiwala, to celebrate their wedding anniversary today (November 23). The video consists of several playful and cosy moments of the husband and wife. Sharing the video, she wrote, 'Happy happiness to us you are the rock of my life. blessed to have you, #happy #wedding #marriage #celebrations #trendingreels #albums #couple #couplegoals'. When it comes to their looks, in the video in some of the pics.

title: ED summons actor Prakash Raj in Rs 100cr fraud case
UP: Faulty brake causes smoke in exp train
description: Rajendra Singh, the public relation officer of Izzatnagar division of North Eastern Railway, said, “Brake binding was observed in train number 15039, following which smoke was detected caused by friction. The brake system was released, and train departed to continue its further journey.”

title: 'These operations are like war': How rescuers plan to free 41 workers trapped in tunnel
description: The ongoing rescue operation to save 41 workers trapped inside Silkyara tunnel in Uttarakhand has reached its final stage. Once the rescue pipe breaks through the debris, NDRF personnel plan to pull out the trapped workers one by one with the help of wheeled stretchers tied to ropes. The NDRF men will go in through the pipe and use their equipment to start sending them out of the tunnel.

title: J&K encounter: Army toll rises to 5; 2 terrorists killed
description: In Jammu and Kashmir's Rajouri district, another soldier lost his life during the ongoing anti-terrorism operation by combined forces of the Army, paramilitary, and J&K police. India has lost five Army personnel, while two Lashkar-e-Taiba terrorists have been neutralized. The conflict started with a search operation based on intelligence about two terrorists in hiding. Sporadic gunfire resulted in the death of two Army captains and two jawans. The pursuit continued the next day, leading to renewed gunfire exchanges near the Line of Control. Weapons and ammunition were recovered from the encounter location.

title: 'When PM encourages you after loss, it raises your confidence': Shami
description: On Prime Minister Narendra Modi's meeting with Team India following their loss to Australia in the ICC World Cup final, Indian pacer Mohammed Shami said that gestures like these give players confidence and are important for them. Another heartbreak was added to the list for Indian fans as Australia beat them by six wickets in the final at Ahmedabad's Narendra Modi Stadium on Sunday, continuing the Men in Blue's drought of ICC trophies since 2013. Australia captured its record-extending sixth World Cup title.

title: Israel-Hamas war: Hostage exchange brings temporary respite
3 from same family murdered by relative in Andhra
description: According to the police, D Srinivas Rao (28) is responsible for stabbing his brother-in-law A Naresh (32), his father A Sambasiva Rao (63), and his mother A Adi Lakshmi (60) in Konanki village of Piduguralla mandal.

title: 'Usually the tournament's best team lifts the trophy': Vaughan trolls Kaif
description: It's been four days since the World Cup ended, but there is still a fight going on as to which team was the best. Was it India, which won 10 games on the trot, or was it Australia, which lost the first two and then won nine straight games, eventually beating India in the final to lift the trophy? From fans to former cricketers, everyone is enjoying this battle on social media platforms, and the latest to join the bandwagon is Michael Vaughan, who on Thursday trolled Mohammad Kaif for terming India as the tournament's best team.

title: Rohit doesn't need to be taught to score hundreds: Ashwin
description: Ravichandran Ashwin said Rohit Sharma "doesn't need to be taught to score hundreds", backing his captain to the hilt after his failure to convert a blazing start into a big score in the World Cup final against Australia attracted criticism. Rohit was in full flow throughout the tournament and the brisk starts that India enjoyed were largely due to his pyrotechnics at the top of the order. Scoring at an incredible strike rate of 125, he amassed 597 runs in 11 matches.

title: EC notice to Rahul for 'panauti', 'pickpocket' remarks
'Never thought that my run at WC would end...': Ashwin
description: Indian star spinner Ravichandran Ashwin fared decently well in the opening match of the World Cup against Australia in Chennai. Despite that he warmed the benches for the remainder of the tournament. Having been on the sidelines of the tournament, Ashwin expressed his pain and disclosed his return was imminent but Hardik Pandya's injury forced the team management to make amends in their planning. Ashwin made it into the 15-member World Cup squad after Axar Patel failed to recover in time from his left quadriceps strain.

title: Strike kills actress performing to Russian troops in Ukraine
description: Polina Menshikh, a Russian actress, was killed while performing in a Russian-controlled area of eastern Ukraine. The incident occurred during a Ukrainian attack in the Donbas region. The attack targeted a school and cultural center in Kumachovo, 60 km from the front line. The Russian defense ministry has not reported any casualties. Ukrainian military commanders claim that the strike was in retaliation for a Russian attack on Ukraine's 128th Separate Mountain Assault Brigade.

title: Cricketer S Sreesanth booked in cheating case
description: Cricketer S Sreesanth, along with two other individuals, Rajiv Kumar and Venkatesh Kini, is facing a police case following a cheating complaint lodged by a man in a northern Kerala district. The complainant, a resident of Choonda, alleges that Rajiv Kumar and Venkatesh Kini received Rs 18.70 lakh on various dates since April 25, 2019, under the pretext of establishing a sports academy in Kollur, Karnataka, where Sreesanth purportedly holds a partnership. According to Sareesh Gopalan, the complainant, he invested the money with the expectation of becoming a partner in the said sports academy.

title: Delhi teen stabs boy 55 times, slits throat and dances
description: The assailant stabbed the victim more than 55 times, slit his throat, and callously dragged the lifeless body through the streets.

title: Sumati Kulkarni murder: Life term for 3; bizman acquitted
description: The convicted individuals — Pradeep Bhat, Mohit Bhat, and Dinesh alias Dinna Rajput — were found guilty of conspiring the murder on the night of January 9, 2017.

title: Mamata: Mahua's expulsion being planned, but ...
Silkyara ops: Railways runs special freight train
description: Zones which are coordinating for the special freight train include East Coast Railway, South Eastern Railway, South East Central Railway, West Central Railway, North Central Railway and Northern Railway.

title: 'Had India won WC...': Abdul Razzaq continues to spit venom
description: Former Pakistani cricketer Abdul Razzaq has made negative comments about Indian cricket, including their defeat to Australia in the ODI World Cup final. He criticized the pitch and claimed that India took advantage of the conditions. Another former Pakistan cricketer, Hasan Raza, had questioned the ICC and BCCI on providing special cricket balls to assist Indian pacers. Former Pakistan captain Inzamam-ul-Haq even claimed that Harbhajan Singh considered converting to Islam, which Harbhajan strongly denied.

title: Animal trailer: Ranbir sets screen on fire with fierce avatar
description: Ranbir Kapoor breaks away from his light-hearted image with Sandeep Vanga Reddy's "Animal," portraying a character marked by intensity, aggression, and pain. Exploring a troubled father-son bond amid underworld chaos, the film, set to release on December 1, challenges Ranbir to delve into new depths, providing a fascinating blend of strength, vulnerability, and unpredictability.

title: Why Mumbai's luxury home sales are shattering records
description: Mumbai's luxury real estate boom premium home sales in Central Mumbai Bandra South Mumbai why Mumbai's luxury housing sales are shattering records

title: Top Lashkar-e-Taiba terrorist killed in Rajouri encounter
description: Security forces in Rajouri district of Jammu and Kashmir have killed a top Lashkar-e-Taiba terrorist named Quari, who was a Pakistani national trained on the Pak-Afghan Front. Quari was believed to be the mastermind behind the Dangri and Kandi attacks and had been active in the region for the past year. He was an expert in IEDs and a trained sniper, as well as skilled in operating and hiding from caves. The ongoing operation against terrorists in Rajouri is being closely monitored by 16 Corps Commander and Rashtriya Rifles' Romeo Force commander.

title: 'Ease of flying': How IndiGo plans to take on Air India
description: The airline plans to modify 35 Airbus A321 aircraft with a dual-class configuration, including a premium cabin featuring eight rows of seats, arranged two on each side. Currently, IndiGo’s Airbus A320 and A321 aircraft offer an average seat pitch of 30 inches. The airline has not yet finalized the additional charges for these premium seats, but customers opting for them can expect benefits like priority boarding, complimentary in-flight food, and more flexibility in itinerary changes. An IndiGo spokesperson declined to comment on these plans.

title: 'We are keen to prove...': Axar urges Team India to 'move on'
description: India's all-rounder, Axar Patel, has urged the team to move on from the disappointment of the World Cup final defeat against Australia. Patel, who missed the ODI World Cup due to injury, expressed his eagerness to contribute to the team. He acknowledged the heartbreak of the World Cup final but emphasized the young team's determination to prove their worth. He highlighted the energy within the squad and the opportunity for the youngsters to showcase their talents.

title: Coach asks girl to send her nude pics to him, held
Way we were cheated was shocking: Samir Kochhar & Varun Bangera
description: The duo has lodged a police complaint against a couple from whom they had purchased two flats.

title: New set of regulations soon to tackle deepfakes: Vaishnaw
description: Union minister for electronics and information technology and communications, Ashwini Vaishnaw, said that a new set of regulations will be introduced soon to tackle deepfakes. ​​He chaired a meeting with social media platforms and stakeholders, on the issue of deepfakes today. Addressing the rising incidents of deepfakes, Vaishnaw said, "Social media platforms agree that clear actionable work is needed to detect and prevent deepfakes and strengthen reporting".

title: Shamita Shetty creates awareness about perimenopause
description: Shamita Shetty, a contestant on Bigg Boss 15, posted a video discussing perimenopause, a condition that is often overlooked. She shared her own experiences with symptoms such as mood swings, sudden weight gain, and fogginess, which many women in her age group can relate to. Perimenopause is a stage that can last up to 10 years before menopause, during which the body prepares for the end of reproductive years. Shamita emphasized the importance of creating awareness about this topic and supporting women through the hormonal changes they go through.

title: OpenAI’s human-threatening model may be reason of Altman’s sacking
description: Prior to OpenAI CEO Sam Altman's firing, staff researchers sent a letter to the board warning about a new AI algorithm called Q* that could pose a threat to humanity. The algorithm, capable of solving certain math problems at a grade-school level, was seen as a major breakthrough by some members of OpenAI. The letter and discovery of the AI model were factors that led to Altman's dismissal, with concerns about hastened commercialization and safety. After Altman's firing, over 700 staff members threatened to resign, leading to his reinstatement.

title: Veteran Gujarati actress Charuben Patel dies due to heart attack
description: Renowned actress Charuben Patel, known for her prolific career in Gujarati drama and film, passed away at the age of 83. Born in Uganda in 1940, Patel began her journey in entertainment while working at the Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation. She had a successful acting career in theater and appeared in over 70 Gujarati films. She also made appearances in Hindi cinema, including films like 'Mirchamsala' and 'Rihaee'. Patel's sudden death came after she was undergoing treatment for a leg fracture.

title: How a 'Mossad agent' helped Ulfa seal its first weapons' deal
Bharti Singh predicts Rubina will be blessed with baby boy
description: Rubina Dilaik has announced that she will be sharing her pregnancy journey in a vlog series. She recently went studio hunting and finalized a space owned by Puneet Pathak. Bharti Singh, who was shooting with Rubina for a pregnancy podcast, expressed her concern for Rubina's health and urged her to go home. Bharti also predicted that Rubina will have a baby boy based on her glowing appearance. During the shoot, Bharti made sure Rubina was comfortable and asked the crew to ensure her safe return home.

title: Watch: Burning Maruti Suzuki Omni in self-driving mode, driver escapes
description: A Maruti Suzuki Omni van caught fire while on the road in Thiruvananthapuram, Kerala. The driver managed to escape before the fire engulfed the vehicle, which was seen moving without anyone driving it in a video.

title: Rohitashv: Can't quit Bhabhiji to break my image as a comedian
description: The actor, who was in Lucknow recently to promote his show Bhabiji Ghar Par Hain!, spoke about wanting to break his image as a comedian

title: 'Wherever they are ...': Israel PM orders Mossad to target Hamas leaders across world
Why most people are suffering from brain fog these days
description: Forgetting things occasionally is normal, but frequent forgetfulness can disrupt daily life. Factors such as information overload, stress, lack of mental stimulation, and poor lifestyle habits contribute to cognitive fog. The pandemic and long COVID can also affect memory and cognitive function. Lack of sleep, a sedentary lifestyle, and a poor diet are common causes of mental fog.  Consulting a healthcare professional is advisable for persistent cognitive difficulties.

title: Shopian freezes at -3.3°C as cold wave sweeps Kashmir
TCS ranks No. 1 for customer satisfaction, here's full report card
description: Tata Consultancy Services (TCS) has been ranked number 1 in service delivery quality and commercial competitiveness in Spain, according to a survey by Whitelane Research. The survey ranked the top 28 IT service providers based on key performance indicators. TCS also improved its position in customer satisfaction, rising to number 2 in Spain. Maria Novoa, Country Head of TCS Spain, credited the company's customer-centric approach and investment in capabilities and innovation for the achievement. Whitelane Research praised TCS for its trusted relationships with customers in Spain.

title: Warner reveals process that led to Aus opting to field in WC final
description: Australia won the ODI World Cup against India, and opener David Warner revealed the unorthodox decision-making process that led to the team opting to chase after winning the crucial toss. Despite statistical indicators favoring batting first, the Australian squad, after a lengthy discussion the night before, opted to chase. Warner shared insights into the team's thought process, stating that despite the stats suggesting batting first, the majority of the team decided to chase.

title: Mysterious pneumonia outbreak in China: All you need to know
description: The outbreak was first reported in northern China, with a significant number of cases involving children. Hospitals in the affected areas reportedly have been overwhelmed with patients showing symptoms of pneumonia, which has not yet been identified or linked to a known pathogen. Primary symptoms reported are consistent with pneumonia, including fever, cough, and difficulty breathing. The WHO has requested detailed information from China regarding the increase in respiratory illnesses and reported clusters of pneumonia.

title: 142 girls harassed here; 15 wrote to Prez, PM
description: The number of minor girls alleging sexual assault and harassment by a school principal in Jind district, Haryana, has risen to 142. The victims claimed they were called to the principal's office and subjected to obscene acts. The case drew attention after 15 girls sent a letter to various authorities in August 2023. The accused was arrested on November 4 and an investigation is underway. The district commissioner has stated that a chargesheet will be prepared against the accused. A special investigation team has been formed to handle the case.

title: Pb cop killed, 2 others injured after Nihang Sikhs open fire
Eying 150 Kmph speed, he knocked down sr cop's son
description: A police team investigating a hit-and-run case in Lucknow has revealed that the accused, Devshri Verma, was encouraging Sarthak Singh to drive at excessive speeds. The incident resulted in the 9-year-old son of a senior police officer being hit. As a result, the police will install zig-zag barricades on affected roads to control vehicle speeds. The accused took the vehicle from his uncle, who was visiting from Kanpur, and drove it around before the incident occurred. Both individuals have admitted to being aware of the lack of police checks in the early morning.

title: Trivia and interesting stats - India vs Australia in T20Is
description: India's 'Gen-Next' cricket team, led by captain Suryakumar Yadav, will face a formidable Australian team in a five-match T20 International series. The series will test young Indian cricketers like Yashasvi Jaiswal, Rinku Singh, Tilak Verma, Jitesh Sharma, and Mukesh Kumar, who have recently made their international debuts. The Australian T20 side will feature World Cup heroes Travis Head, Glenn Maxwell, Adam Zampa, and Steve Smith, as well as IPL performers.

title: Class IV Jajpur student made to do sit-ups, dies
BCA degree holder arrested for Rs 80 lakh sim-swap fraud
description: A 24-year-old man from Pune has been arrested by the cybercrime branch for allegedly stealing Rs 80 lakh from a businessman's account through a sim swap fraud. The accused, Gautam Mukherjee, had been involved in this fraudulent activity for about two years and was working with a gang. Mukherjee and his accomplices deactivated the simcard of the businessman, got a new one issued, and withdrew Rs 79.70 lakh. The police have frozen Rs 50 lakh and returned it to the complainant. Mukherjee and his associates were working with a gang of cybercriminals based in Nigeria.

title: Dravid not keen on contract extension; Laxman set to be next India coach
description: Rahul Dravid has decided not to continue as the head coach of the Indian cricket team after their defeat in the World Cup final. Dravid's two-year contract ended with the conclusion of the tournament, and he has communicated his decision to the BCCI. VVS Laxman is set to replace Dravid as the head coach. Laxman, who is currently the head coach of a second-string Indian team, has expressed his keenness for the job and is likely to sign a long-term contract. Dravid may take on a role at the National Cricket Academy in Bengaluru and is in talks with an IPL team for a contract.

title: Trainee pilot loses contact with ATC, lands on airport taxiway
description: A woman trainee pilot from Indira Gandhi Rashtriya Udan Akademi in Rae Bareli lost contact with air traffic control (ATC) and landed on a taxiway instead of the main runway at Nagpur's Dr Babasaheb Ambedkar International airport. The pilot had taken off from Gondia and was flying solo. After losing contact with ATC, she landed on the parallel taxiway. The incident has been reported to the Directorate General of Civil Aviation (DGCA), and an inquiry will be conducted to determine the next steps.

title: 'Hyderabad to be renamed Bhagyanagar if ...'
May ask 7-Judge bench to rule on validity of sedition law: CJI
description: The Supreme Court is considering a plea to have a seven-judge bench rule on the constitutionality of the sedition provision under Section 124A of the IPC. The plea argues that a five-judge bench may not be suitable due to a previous ruling that upheld the validity of the provision. The Chief Justice of India (CJI) will decide on the matter soon. In September, the CJI-led bench rejected the government's plea to pause the judicial scrutiny of the provision.

title: At hearing on death penalty, amicus, lawyers back abolition
description: Lawyers present at a Supreme Court hearing on reducing instances of the death penalty in India expressed their support for its abolition. They argued that the use of the death penalty should be further limited by expanding the list of mitigating factors and implementing periodic psychological evaluations of convicts. They also advocated for giving adequate time to convicted individuals to present mitigating circumstances before sentencing. The Supreme Court initiated the proceedings to establish guidelines for considering mitigating circumstances in death penalty cases.

title: Idle spouse can’t burden partner with maintenance liability: HC
description: The Delhi High Court has ruled that a spouse who is capable of earning but chooses to remain unemployed cannot burden the other partner with maintenance liability. The court reduced the monthly maintenance amount from Rs 30,000 to Rs 21,000 to be paid by a man to his estranged wife under the Hindu Marriage Act. The court emphasized that maintenance should be provided to the spouse who is unable to support themselves and that both husband and wife's rights and obligations should be examined.

title: How this Ghaziabad gang used malicious ads links to empty out accounts
description: The gang would place ads on the internet that led people to fake websites resembling popular e-commerce portals. Female telecallers pretended to be customer care representatives and convinced people to follow steps that resulted in money being taken from their accounts. The gang operated across multiple states and duped at least 15 people, with transactions totaling more than Rs 25-30 lakh. The leader of the gang, Shahrukh Akhtar, lived a lavish lifestyle with the money he cheated from victims.

title: HP bans trekking above 3,000m in Kangra, Kullu & Kinnaur dists
description: Trekking above 3,000 metres has been banned in Kangra and Kinnaur districts of Himachal Pradesh due to approaching winters. Prior permission would be required for treks below 3,000 metres and action will be taken against those violating the orders. Paragliding activities near Dhauladhar mountains in Kangra district have also been banned. The ban is enforced in winters due to the risk of trekking in changing weather conditions. The president of the Parvati Valley Adventure Tour Operators' Association suggests setting up check posts on trekking routes for better administration and rescue operations.

title: Far-right, anti-Islam Wilders to win Dutch elections
description: The far-right, anti-Islam PVV party led by Geert Wilders achieved a significant victory in the Dutch elections, securing 35 seats in parliament. This outcome represents a shift to the right in the Netherlands and raises concerns in Brussels due to the PVV's call for a referendum on EU membership. Wilders faces challenges in forming a stable government and will need to build a broad coalition. Immigration was a key issue in the campaign, with Wilders advocating for strict measures.

title: In busy IPO week on Dalal Street, 5 cos look to raise 7.4k cr
Dog bites 29 in an hour on busy Chennai road, beaten to death
description: A stray dog in Chennai bit 29 people in less than an hour before being killed by locals who suspected it may have been rabid. Witnesses said the dog suddenly attacked pedestrians, biting their ankles and feet. Of those attacked, 24 had deep cuts and bleeding, with possible saliva transfer. The injured were admitted to a nearby hospital, where they received treatment for rabies prevention. The Greater Chennai Corporation rounded up 32 dogs for observation. Rabies tests can only be done on dead dogs, making it difficult to confirm if the dog was infected.

title: New DDA units: Luxury penthouses, golf course
description: The Delhi Development Authority (DDA) is offering luxury penthouses as part of its Festival Special Housing Scheme. The penthouses, located in Dwarka's Sector 19B, feature terrace gardens and panoramic views of a golf course. Priced between Rs 4.5 crore and Rs 5 crore, the penthouses offer opulent design, cutting-edge technology, and optimal ventilation. The project also includes affordable flats and will set a precedent for future urban development initiatives. Registration for the flats will begin soon.

title: 'Over 50% of individuals get I-T refunds in a month'
Adobe buys Indian generative AI startup: What makes it important
description: Adobe has acquired Rephrase.ai, a Bengaluru-based startup that runs an AI-powered video creation platform. The deal will allow Adobe to integrate Rephrase's technology with its Creative Cloud video-editing platform, enhancing its offerings. Rephrase.ai provides a text-to-video generation platform that simplifies the process of creating professional-looking videos. The majority of Rephrase's team members will join Adobe as part of the deal. This acquisition marks Adobe's first foray into the generative AI and video-tooling space and makes Rephrase the first Indian startup to be acquired by the company.

title: Inside U'khand tunnel, 'chor-police' help trapped bust stress
description: Trapped workers in the collapsed Silkyara tunnel have found ways to pass the time and alleviate stress while awaiting rescue. They have been playing games such as 'chor-police', teen patti, and rummy. The authorities have provided them with playing cards and a stash of khaini to prevent withdrawal symptoms. Medical experts at the site believe that while the workers may experience psychological changes after being in darkness for so long, they will ultimately be fine.

title: ‘Kin glued to TV to keep track of final phase of rescue operation’
description: Family members of workers trapped inside the Silkyara tunnel in Uttarakhand are both excited and nervous about their safe evacuation. They anxiously wait outside the tunnel, constantly updating their relatives about the rescue operation. Meanwhile, in Kotdwar town, a teenager plans to throw a party for his father, who has been a source of motivation for the trapped individuals. However, they are all urged to wait for official confirmation before celebrating.

title: Olympics bid: Ahmedabad embarks on 20-yr plan
description: The Ahmedabad Urban Development Authority (Auda) has initiated a 20-year development plan called Ahmedabad Development Plan 2041 in preparation for the bid to host the 2036 Olympics. Auda is engaging stakeholders for insights on the bid process and is also working on a new general development control regulation. Auda has issued a tender to appoint a consultant to develop a master plan addressing water supply, sewage, and drainage needs until 2050. The plan focuses on eco-sensitive and sustainable urban growth, including groundwater conservation and innovative water management strategies. The master plan will cover areas within Auda, the designated venue for the Olympic Games.

title: India, Australia to kick off defence drill in Perth today
description: Soon after India and Australia decided to further crank up their defence ties with an eye firmly on China’s aggressive behaviour in the Indo-Pacific, the two countries are all set to kick off the bilateral ‘AustraHind’ tri-Service combat exercise at Perth from Thursday. Australia has also invited India as an “active participant” in its largest multination biennial exercise ‘Talisman Sabre’ in 2025. India had sent only observers for this year’s edition of the exercise in July-August.​

title: ​Pulao, roti, sabzi: First hot meal for workers after 11 days
description: After being stranded for 11 days, the 41 workers in the Silkyara tunnel in India finally received a hearty meal. The food was delivered through a six-inch supply pipe inserted through the rubble. In addition to food, the workers also received essential supplies and a modified communication system, which has improved interaction between the workers and rescue teams. The workers are reported to be safe and communication with them has become clearer.

​41 ambulances, 2 helicopters ready to ferry the rescued to hospital
description: As hopes rise for the evacuation of 41 workers trapped in an under-construction tunnel in Uttarkashi's Silkyara, preparations are being made to transport them to hospitals. Ambulances and helicopters are on standby, with at least one ambulance per person and a 40-bed Covid ward available for medical assistance. Two helicopters have also been prepared for use by the disaster management team. Health experts have warned that the trapped workers may face health issues such as respiratory diseases and lack of Vitamin D due to their prolonged confinement.

Wrong tiger tranquilised? NTCA seeks report from MP forest dept
description: The National Tiger Conservation Authority (NTCA) has sought a report from the Madhya Pradesh forest department following complaints that the wrong tiger was tranquilised and captured in Seoni, Madhya Pradesh. TOI had reported on November 9 that an MP forest team, out to nab a tiger that has killed six people in six weeks, may have darted the wrong tiger near Pench Tiger Reserve, since another woman was killed by a tiger in the same area just three hours later.

Bihar eyes ‘TN-like’ legal shield for quota hike law in 9th schedule
description: To insulate the increased reservation for deprived classes in Bihar from judicial intervention, the Nitish Kumar cabinet approved a resolution to request the Centre for including the state legislation on quota hike in the 9th schedule of Constitution. The cabinet also cleared a proposal demanding special category status for Bihar, as it will ease the burden in implementing five poverty alleviation schemes worth Rs 2.5 lakh crore for the upliftmnt of 94 lakh poor families “in less than five years”.

title: Missing papers, Congress fissures stall Karnataka caste census
description: The Karnataka government has delayed its plan to accept the controversial caste census report due to internal divisions within the Congress party and opposition from dominant communities. The chairperson of the Karnataka Backward Classes Commission has been granted an extension to complete the report, with only the worksheets missing. The report has faced opposition from major caste groups, including the Lingayats and Vokkaligas, who have criticized it as "unscientific".

title: 2nd ED chargesheet against fugitive arms dealer Sanjay Bhandari
description: The Enforcement Directorate (ED) has filed a chargesheet against fugitive defence dealer Sanjay Bhandari, naming two other accused — NRI businessman CC Thampi, who was arrested in 2020 by the agency in a money laundering case, and one S Chadha. This is the second chargesheet filed against Bhandari who is engaged in a grim battle to defeat India’s effort for his extradition from the UK where he is currently based. He is wanted in India for allegedly receiving payoffs in several defence deals through his UAE-registered shell firms.
